cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the evaluation of word embeddings, which is a topic related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a typology of approaches to evaluation, which suggests a focus on methodology and experimentation, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of word embeddings also involves artificial intelligence techniques, which could place the paper in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evaluation of word embeddings can also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
